step 1:-
===============
Make a project in react
create rempsitory and upload in git repo

step 2
======================

REFERENCE LINK = https://create-react-app.dev/docs/deployment#github-pages

======================================

Add home url  =
===============
"homepage": "http://mywebsite.com/relativepath",
  
  like = https://mdmuzaffer.github.io/react // first username .github.io / repo
  
  step 3
  =================
  npm install --save gh-pages //install
  
  ==> To publish it at https://myusername.github.io/my-app, run:
  
  Step 4
  ====================
  
  Add the following scripts in your package.json:
  
  
    "scripts": {
+   "predeploy": "npm run build",
+   "deploy": "gh-pages -d build",
    "start": "react-scripts start",
    "build": "react-scripts build",
    
    
    =================================
    
    Step 5
    ===================
    
    Tweak your package.json scripts to push deployments to master:
    
     "scripts": {
    "predeploy": "npm run build",
-   "deploy": "gh-pages -d build",
+   "deploy": "gh-pages -b master -d build",
    
    
    Step 6
    =========================
    
    Step 3: Deploy the site by running npm run deploy
    
    npm run deploy
    
    ================================
    
    Step7
    ===================
    
    Step 4: For a project page, ensure your projectâ€™s settings use
    
    Finally, make sure GitHub Pages option in your GitHub project settings is set to use the gh-pages branch:
    
    Example = https://github.com/mdmuzaffer/react/settings/pages
    
    Select here  = GitHub Pages
    
    
